deck_excerpt: Nightmare Throne = 3 more copies of Called By to counter Ash Blossom on Branded Fusion!
deck_description:
Nearly two years of Branded has existed in Masterduel, and we still get cool new ways to play the archetype! Yubel remains the best way to play Branded, and its powerups is an indirect buff to Albaz and friends. In addition to the regular playstyle of Branded, Yubel can now be used as a monster negate engine - effectively granting the deck an extra 3 copies of Called by the Grave. The Yubel cards are fairly minimal and it is composed of 5 cards. It is comprised of 3 Nightmare Throne, 1 Spirit of Yubel and 1 OG Yubel. Upon activation, Nightmare Throne destroys in deck Spirit of Yubel, which floats into the OG Yubel from deck. From there, a Phantom of Yubel can be summoned, granting Branded another way to deal with handtraps like Ash Blossom! Phantom of Yubel grants a higher success rate for Branded Fusion to successfully resolve - thus winning you more games! 

Yubel can also break boards and bait handtraps, since most gamestates are monster interaction based nowadays, the opposing player will be forced to prematurely use their interruption in an effort to stop Phantom of Yubel from coming out! After Yubel has sufficiently used up your opponent's interruption, you can go for your regular Branded plays unimpeded, without fear of Ash Blossom or Nibiru! 
 
The Yubel cards also aren't really "bricks" since they can be discarded to the GY as part of your Branded combos. If you happen to have both Yubels in the GY (through Branded Fusion, Grass Grows Greener, etc.) you can also make Phantom of Yubel relatively free! 

While not entirely game changing and it doesn't largely change the strategy, the "Yubel engine" grants another layer of protection of Branded. I highly recommend my fellow Branded bros to try out this next evolution of Albaz and friends!
 
Also, if you want a proper guide and combos how to pilot Branded, check out my earlier guide by clicking here.
 
Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!
 
GLHF Duelists!

This variant of HERO Beat uses an engine consisting of King of the Swamp, Polymerization, and Elemental HERO Woodsman for more fusion shenanigans! King of the Swamp can search for Polymerization, which allows you to fuse cards in your hand or on your field. You can also use it as fusion material for Elemental HERO Absolute Zero because it's a water monster. Finally, Elemental HERO Woodsman has an effect that allows you to search for or recycle Polymerization during your standby phase and has a high defense stat; it's a great card for staging a comingback against a tough opponent.

deck_description:
I believe this could run in a 45-50 card deck without sacrificing too much consistency. But what I have right now is a 40 card deck instead :)

This deck pushes out 1 card & discard combo consistently. Having Sage on hand means a full board.

A lot of option and routes for an end board but if you are ever planning on summoning magia always, you need the ritual monster. losing one in a combo means no magia. But even without magia, the end board is just.... just... ...spicy.

P.S. This deck is also inspired from a YT video utilizing buster blader in the deck. It is nice, but the buster cards does take more card slots that could've been used for other extenders, interrupts or card consistency.

deck_excerpt: Petit Dragon The ultimate normal monster, blue eyes is like an ant to him.
deck_description: This deck is amazing, doing everything with petit dragon it accomplishes that which neer mortals dream of. Using his brother, ringowurm, petit dragon can synchro climb into any rank 10 accel synchro monster. (I just went with stardust warrior because barrone is banned but it used to be barrone) Ultra Polymerization is fantastic for both summoning first of the dragons and bringing our lord and savior back to the field to use for a  gachi gachi to crash and protecc itself so you can summon zeus. Fun fact: first of the dragons is unaffected by zeus so it can survive the nuke. the instant fusion is used for the level 2 allvain which is just amazing for either synchro, xyz or link plays. One of your dragons get banished? bring that dude back with the guarddragon pisty! dont know what to do with 2 petit dragons? make a spheres and get the third one out of the deck! Afraid of ash? Sales Ban it. Heck even borrelsword can be summoned using link spiders and masq, Meaning its a towers! I have worked for almost a year now to profect this deck and I hope everyone enjoys it!   All praise the lord petit!

deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Joshua Kirby

Tournament: Fredericton WCQ Regional – September 22nd 2024

Placement: Top 4
Funmeter: Maximum! Let's have a funtabulous duel!

Welcome! If you recall, I had a blast with Bremen Musicians. Now, a bird wants to be independent with its arising heart. Let's burn it up!

 

 

Gameplan

1) Discard Enchanter + Parasite to GY with Ravenous. Next, when you have four monsters and nothing more, Link Summon Saryuja and Special Summon Black Luster Soldier with its ability but don't banish Ancient and Level 1 DARK monsters by accident. Then, place ME-PSY-YA on Pendulum Zone to unlock "Primal Seed" loop.

2) Use "Monster Reborn" to revive Ancient alongside two more monsters but reserve 2 x Level 1 monsters for future use. Next, play "Galaxy Queen's Light" and target on Ancient, setting the level of your monsters to 7. Then, XYZ Summon Arise-Heart with these three, right behind any Extra Monster Zone (EMZ) to your preference.

3) Revive a monster and Link Summon Reprodocus with it and Saryuja, above where Arise-Heart is. Next, revive Enchanter. Then, bring forth 2 x Level 1 monsters excluding Parasite and XYZ Summon Promenade...

  • If you have noticed, playing "Primal Seed" feeds Arise-Heart and we can progress even further with Enchanter. So long as you don't discard Sanctuary + Reborn by accident besides "Primal Seed" with Enchanter, which are your combo pieces, all is well.

4) When Arise-Heart has 20 or more materials, activate Reprodocus to change the Type of Arise-Heart to Winged Beast. Next, play Sanctuary and attach Arise-Heart into Promenade.

5) Finally, revive Parasite and Fusion Summon Nightingale by using Parasite + Promenade as materials. Raise the level of Nightingale and launch some fireworks for your glorious victory!

 

If you wonder how to save up some SR and UR points, I can show you:

- "Monster Reborn" is given for free, if you have completed the tutorial to save 30 UR!

- "Pot of Avarice" can be collected by purchasing "Re-Contract Universe" deck. 90 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Black Luster Soldier - Envoy of the Beginning" can be collected by purchasing "Spiral Spear Strike" deck. 30 UR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Wonder Wand" and "Spellbook of Knowledge" can be collected by purchasing "Spellbook of Prophecy" deck. 120 SR saved and you can try a new deck!

- "Into The Void" + "Allure of Darkness" can be found within "The Infinite Void" Secret Pack to save 180 SR!

- "Lyrilusc - Independent Nightingale" + "Lyrilusc - Promenade Thrush" can be found within "Moonlit Avian Dance" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "Pot of Acquistiveness" + "Ravenous" + "Primal Seed" + "Fusion Parasite" can be found within "Legacy Pack" to save 90 SR and 60 UR!

- "T.G. Hyper Librarian" can be found within "Futuristic Creatures" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Kashtira Arise-Heart" can be found within "A Warrior of Seething Anger" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

- "Formula Synchron" can be found within "Stardust Ties" Secret Pack to save 60 SR!

- "Moray of Avarice" can be found within "Treasures of the Cosmic Ocean" Secret Pack to save 30 UR!

 

So, in total, you can save up to 600 SR and 210 UR, if you are willing to spend some gems. Other SR and UR cards I didn't mention are essential.

 

That's all for this one. If you have any questions, feel free to ask. Have fun in Master Duel!

deck_excerpt: Branded Despia with Azamina package with Hand Traps
deck_description:
The new Azamina Omni-negate works really well here as it is a Fusion monster meaning it has synergy with Branded and doesnt lock you out of Branded Fusion, Sacred Azamina being treated as a fusion summon also gives it the protection off of Branded Lost and can potentially be a starter if you need the search off of Lost.

Thrown in Handtraps instead of extra engine or boardbreakers as i feel post ROTA format will be dominated by Fuwaross and not playing it feels bad. tried to keep it as close to 40-45 as possible to maximize chances of opening a way to Branded Fusion (Aluber/Opening/Branded Fusion) and a way to Azamina. Wanted is the ideal draw as you can banish for the Draw 1 to counter the discard from Black Witch. Side and Handtraps still very much undecided at this point as we need to see how the format develops

Melffy's have the ability to set up consistently powerful but underwhelming endboards making it perfect for the 4 player format. Not to mention its capacity to interact with every single turn that is played, slowly shifting the power back to yourself when your turn comes around. At the same time as this however, this deck list has the incrediable capacity to just end simple, play slow and wait on traps, you can summon a melffy catty, set 3 and hold some cards like maxx c or swift scarecrow, allowing you to take your time developing into something more powerful as everyone tears eachother to shredds. In doing this however you do run the risk of getting OTK'd, as without the right opening hand, you will not be able to just hold onto your cards. This is why I have chosen rescue cat as my DM, Rescue cat has the amazing ability to get you litterally anything you need. Most games I found myself fully commiting to the first turn play, having to wall up with a melffy wally and a few defensive cards. Summoning kerass and ojama pink from deck off Cat to make Melffy of the Forest, searching out wally who will summon pony and puppy. Pony would bring back Kerass for turn 2 and puppy would summon any melffy needed for the situation. It is a versitile consistently annoying midrange deck with some funny little options like: the one polly for a 2 card off rescue cat Koalo-Koala, pinpoint landing providing draw power, grave of the super ancient organism stumping most decks and Nat beast turn one with a full hand of melffy's and a red reboot.

As for end goals of the deck, there is very few possibilities. You either punch in with big extra-deck bodies, or sit on looping melffies and Ronin Racoon until everyone kills eachother.
Pure variant of Fire King witht the new Ulkanix card

normal stein -> pay tax -> summon Geo Kraken -> search mystic mine or chicken game. smile :)

other options:

Dragoon pass

open one for one or magical scientist for spright plays.

open machina engine for machina plays.

open nothing but battle traps and life gain and hope you dont die.

Summon Cyber end, Machina Ruinforce or Carnot the Eternal Machine -> limiter removal -> Mystic wok, Enchanted Javelin, Altar for tribute or Destruct potion ... +<8000 lp.

 

The magical scientist end board off one for one is: 2 counter Savage, Abomination in emz, and Cyberse Desavewurm in grave. you work with what you get dealt, but this deck is so funny I had to share.

deck_excerpt: Machina for Edison format, No Gadgets.
deck_description: Machina is one of the strongest decks in Edison, albeit limited by 2 of the biggest blowouts around, System Down and Fortress Dragon.  Dropping the Gadgets gets extra tools to play through those blowouts and reduces the clogged hands that just have a bunch of low impact normal summons.  Book of Moon is just great here, not only does it represent a point of interaction and a form of pseudo removal, but it can also protect Fortress from a lot of the banishing Removal like Prison, Bottomless and the aforementioned System Down.  Junk Synchron really plays well here with all the 2s I tend to have in rotation between Ryko and Peacekeeper, and the Hampster and Gearframe that can go get them.  Upstarts are chosen over draw traps since they give more chances to see Gearframe and Fortress and act faster than the traps, which this deck tends to value.  The Side is mostly a bunch of control and removal options, but Iron Wall is something that is basically mandatory to come in from the board every game, since it creates insurance against the banishing removal while checking things like DAD, Caius and Vayu.  Otherwise its pretty straightforward, Gearframe gets and protects Fortress, Peacekeeper is there to get if you have Gearframe and Fortress, Force is a full discard by itself.
Know this from the start: bring your best or don't waste my time!

fire king is a really cheap alternative for a good tier 2 deck, but of course it needs ulcanix to work properly, anyway it is a interesting mid-range deck with a lot of skill expression

pros:

  • cheap 

  • 14/15 cards for non-engine

  • mid-range with good going first and second 

  • good grind game

  • open extra deck 

  • in engine interaction with a spell and monster negate

  • layer interaction

cons:

  • can brick, it has 11 starters but they require 1 fire monster in addition

  • the deck has some bricks like high avatar garunix, the card is strong it can activate your sacred garunix in grave during your opponent’s turn, at 2 makes you able to activate ulcanix 2 times 

  • weak to hand traps (even 2 ash can be a problem)

  • can be hard to pilot 

the best mid-range as of now that you can play in master duel, it is a solid option and i think the list can be improved.
